00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:15,000
 And I want to acknowledge them because you're going to see their thumbprints all over the series as we work our way through.

138
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:21,000
 But as we begin, we've got to talk about what is joy before we can talk about where is joy.

139
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:26,000
 Because before we can learn how to experience it, we need to unpack the essence of it.

140
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:28,000
 Because therein lies the problem for so many of us.

141
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:32,000
 Like, without knowing what joy is, we won't know where to look for it.

142
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:42,000
 So recently, just a couple months ago, I found myself in Target trying to pull together the biggest birthday bash possible for my wife.

143
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,000
 She had turned 30, and so it was a big deal.

144
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:49,000
 Like, I needed to make sure that we had all of the markings of a good birthday celebration at the home.

145
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:55,000
 And so I went into Target, I was looking for confetti, and I was trying to find streamers, and I wanted to find a card and some flowers,

146
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:58,000
 and I wanted to find those big, foiled balloons.

147
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,000
 You know which ones I'm talking about?

148
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:02,000
 The ones that everybody loves to blow up and have for their birthday?

149
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:04,000
 That was the object of what I was looking for.

150
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:10,000
 And so I walk into Target, I make my way over to the arts and crafts section, and the balloons are nowhere to be found.

151
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,000
 Makes no sense.

152
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,000
 This is exactly where they should be.

153
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:15,000
 This is decor for my wife's birthday.

154
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,000
 Where are the balloons?

155
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:21,000
 And so I make a lap around Target, I take another lap around Target, I make a third lap around Target,

156
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:33,000
 and now, so frustrated, I find an employee, and I humble myself before them, and I ask them, "Where are the foiled, big, numbered balloons?"

157
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:51,000
 And they said to me, "They are not in the arts and crafts section. They are in the party supplies section."

158
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:57,000
 You see, I thought I knew what I was looking for, but I was mistaken.

159
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:00,000
 It's not arts and crafts. It's party supplies.

160
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:06,000
 And the minute I had clarified what it was, I knew where to go and look for it.

161
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,000
 So what is joy?

162
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:12,000
 If you don't know what it is, you will not know where to find it.

163
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:15,000
 So here's a definition for you.

164
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:27,000
 Joy is a lasting emotion that is not achieved in life, but received from God, who felt it first and feels it most.

165
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:36,000
 Joy is a lasting emotion that is not achieved in life, but received from God, who felt it first and feels it most.

166
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:45,000
 Which may come as a surprise to some of us, because when we think of what mood God is actually in, joy does not normally spring top of mind.

167
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,000
 It doesn't crack the top ten.

168
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:51,000
 Instead, something different likely comes to mind.

169
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:57,000
 When we picture the face of God as he's staring back at us, we interpret a different mood altogether.

170
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,000
 Like, just try it for yourself for a minute.

171
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:03,000
 When you think of what mood God is in, what do you come up with?

172
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:06,000
 This is not rhetorical. This is conversational.

173
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:12,000
 What mood do you see on God's face as he looks at you right now here tonight?

174
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,000
 Proud?

175
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,000
 What else?

176
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,000
 Disappointment?

177
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:22,000
 Delighted?

178
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,000
 Joy, love?

179
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,000
 Faithful?

180
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,000
 Happy?

181
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,000
 Anybody else?

182
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,000
 Patient?

183
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,000
 Okay, here's what's fascinating about the answers we just gave.

184
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:39,000
 So many of the answers we gave are attributes of God.

185
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:42,000
 They're not attitudes of God.

186
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:53,000
 You see, often what we think about when we think of the mood of God is we look at him, and what we find is we're not comfortable with the attitude he may be showing,

187
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:58,000
 and so we'll ascribe an aptitude instead, because the attitude we may see is we may see that he is disappointed.

188
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:02,000
 That's one that has hung over my life for so very long.

189
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:04,000
 Maybe we look at him and we see that he's angry.

190
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,000
 He could be frustrated.

191
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:08,000
 He might be indifferent or apathetic or annoyed.

192
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:22,000
 I don't know what mood you may see on the face of God, and yet what we know is that when we consider who God is, not who we are, but who he actually is, joy is a really logical mood for him to take.

193
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:34,000
 Dallas Willard says it like this, "Central to the understanding and proclamation of the Christian gospel today is a re-visioning of what God's own life is like and how the physical cosmos fits into it.

194
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:40,000
 It is a great and important task to come to terms with what we really think when we think of God.

195
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:44,000
 We should, to begin with, think that God leads a very interesting life."

196
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,000
 I love that.

197
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:49,000
 He must lead a very interesting life, and that he is full of joy.

198
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:55,000
 Undoubtedly, he is the most joyous being in the universe.

199
00:15:55,000 --> 00:16:05,000
 You see, fundamental to finding joy is the understanding that God is the most joyous being in the universe.

200
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:09,000
 And it doesn't take long to learn that this is the case in the scripture.

201
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:12,000
 Like, you just turn to page one.

202
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:23,000
 You read Genesis chapter one, and what you find is that God is making day after day after day, and he is consistently attributing to them goodness.

203
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:28,000
 He says, "That one's good, and that one's good, and oh, when you look, that one's good, the fourth one's good as well."

204
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:31,000
 He runs the full gamut and finds they're all good.

205
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:34,000
 Listen, God is not full of himself.

206
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,000
 He is not self-inflated.

207
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,000
 He is not easily impressed.

208
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,000
 God is truthful.

209
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:42,000
 And so when he says that these days are good, it's because they are.

210
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,000
 They're good days.

211
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:53,000
 And yet what you see as he talks to Job later in the Old Testament, as he's describing the creation narrative, he says,

212
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:56,000
 "Where were you when I laid the earth's foundations?

213
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,000
 Tell me if you understand.

214
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,000
 Who marked off its dimensions?

215
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,000
 Surely you know.

216
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,000
 Who stretched a measuring line across it?

217
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:03,000
 On what were its footings set?

218
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,000
 Or who laid its cornerstone?

219
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:11,000
 While the morning stars sang together and all the angels shouted for joy."

