00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:19,000
 You see, God wants to remind us tonight of what he's done.

300
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:34,000
 Yes, as we look through the Old Testament that he delivered his people out of Egypt and he moved them through the wilderness and he forgave their sins and he blessed their harvest and he made sure to preserve their families and legacies forever.

301
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:38,000
 But we also should remember what he's done in our life.

302
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:47,000
 We should recall and recollect and even share with one another the goodness of God in our day.

303
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:57,000
 Because every single example is a declaration of his joyfulness and the joy he wants you to come into.

304
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:00,000
 You see, God is joyful at heart.

305
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:02,000
 He wants you to be the same.

306
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:09,000
 He wants you to be very happy, which puts some of you on your heels.

307
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:12,000
 Like, you hear that and you're like, "Whoa, hold on.

308
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:17,000
 That feels like a massive contradiction to everything I ever learned in church growing up.

309
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,000
 God doesn't want me to be happy.

