00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:22,000
 He doesn't care about how I feel.

312
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:24,000
 He only cares about my character.

313
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:29,000
 He doesn't care about what I'm doing so long as I'm doing it like Jesus, right?

314
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:33,000
 God is much more interested in me becoming like Christ than anything else.

315
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:39,000
 And yet, I wouldn't disagree with you nor would the author of Hebrews, but listen to what he says about Jesus.

316
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:43,000
 He says, "You have loved righteousness and hated lawlessness.

317
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:52,000
 This is why God, your God, has anointed you with the oil of joy beyond your companions."

318
00:23:52,000 --> 00:24:02,000
 If our walk is a walk where we get to become like that, joyful beyond comparison, I'm in.

319
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:04,000
 Like, that sounds pretty awesome.

320
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:12,000
 Like, yes, everything God is doing is trying to form you into the image of his son, as Romans 8 would say.

321
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:18,000
 And the image of his son is one that has a joy which surpasses that of anybody else.

322
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:21,000
 Like, Jesus is incomparably happy.

323
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:23,000
 He is exceptionally glad.

324
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:29,000
 He is supremely pleasant, so pleasant that no one else can even come close in comparison.

325
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:34,000
 And if you don't take that or me for enough evidence, then just look at the life of Christ.

326
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:40,000
 Like, his birth was heralded as good news of great joy for all people, Luke 2.10.

327
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:45,000
 His kingdom was proclaimed as a place of everlasting joy, Romans 14.17.

328
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:50,000
 So cheerful was Jesus in life that people claimed he was a glutton and a drunkard.

329
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:53,000
 Listen, you don't get a reputation like that by being a stick in the mud.

