00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:56,000
 You know what, man? You have too much to eat and you might have too much to drink.

331
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:58,000
 You look a little too happy with yourself.

332
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,000
 That's Luke 7.34.

333
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:05,000
 He performed miracles that astounded crowds and sent the sick rejoicing, Matthew 15.30.

334
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:08,000
 He was happy in the Holy Spirit, Luke 10.21.

335
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:13,000
 His life's work was the joy of saving people, Luke 15.3-7.

336
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:18,000
 He joyfully endured the cross, despising its shame, Hebrews 12.2.

337
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:23,000
 And he gives joy to all that see him.

338
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:31,000
 A joy that will never, ever be taken away, John 16.22.

339
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:44,000
 Jesus is far more full of glee and gladness and gaiety than you think.

