00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:17,000
 They are paired together. Psalm 32, 11.

356
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:22,000
 Rejoice in the Lord and be happy, you who are godly.

357
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:26,000
 Shout for joy, all you who are morally upright.

358
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:32,000
 Psalm 68, 3. But may the righteous be glad and rejoice before God.

359
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:34,000
 May they be happy and joyful.

360
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:38,000
 Psalm 100, 1 and 2. Sing to the Lord all the world.

361
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:43,000
 Worship the Lord with joy. Come before him with happy songs.

362
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:47,000
 Psalm 118, 24. This is the day that the Lord has made.

363
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:52,000
 Let us rejoice and be glad or happy in it.

364
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:55,000
 I could keep going, but you get the point.

365
00:27:55,000 --> 00:28:06,000
 You cannot drain joy of its emotional element and call it joy.

366
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:11,000
 Yet so many of us do this so very often.

367
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:17,000
 You see, so many of us have fallen prey that this is the life God has called us to live.

368
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:24,000
 Like for so many, Christianity, it's about doing the right things more than feeling the right way.

369
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:27,000
 Like it's all about religious creeds and observances.

370
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:30,000
 That I come to church on Sundays and I give when the plate passes.

371
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:33,000
 And I attend group on the weekdays.

