00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 He's not interested in your religious compliance.

400
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:56,000
 What he is interested in is the happiness of your soul.

401
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:59,000
 That's what he wants for you.

402
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:06,000
 Like in a way, unhappiness in our life should be a red flag or a signal flare.

403
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:09,000
 That something needs to change.

404
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:14,000
 Like no different than if you woke up tomorrow morning and your back hurt.

405
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:17,000
 "Oh, yeah, like rough night."

406
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:20,000
 And you went to sleep again and you woke up and it was still hurting.

407
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 And you went to sleep again and it was still hurting.

408
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:34,000
 You wouldn't likely respond by saying, "You know what? It's making me tougher."

409
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:38,000
 Instead, you'd get rid of the mattress.

410
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:41,000
 You would dispose of it quickly.

411
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:47,000
 You would make sure to take note of the fact that this isn't the way my sleep should be conducted.

412
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:50,000
 I'm left feeling worse. I should feel better.

413
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:53,000
 It should raise a concern.

414
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:55,000
 And yet here's the thing, porch.

415
00:31:55,000 --> 00:32:02,000
 Too often we are willing to tolerate our spiritual discomfort because it's just what we're supposed to do.

416
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:07,000
 I'm just supposed to walk with God even though it doesn't feel right.

417
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:11,000
 I'm just supposed to read my Bible even though I haven't gotten anything out of it in weeks.

418
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:14,000
 I'm just supposed to confess my sin even though no one's actually holding me accountable.

419
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:18,000
 I'm just supposed to go to church even though I'm just going to keep up appearances.

420
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:22,000
 We do all of the right things, but we don't feel any of the right way.

421
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:26,000
 And that should be deeply disturbing to us.

422
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:29,000
 It's deeply disturbing to God.

423
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:31,000
 He doesn't want that for you.

424
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:35,000
 Now listen, I'm not saying that there is not a place for discipline in your life.

425
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:37,000
 We're going to talk about it.

426
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:39,000
 And yet just within the concept of what joy is,

