00:33:49,000 --> 00:34:00,000
 G.K. Chesterton said this, and this quote was what began my deliverance from joyless despair.

444
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:05,000
 He said, "Joy, which was the small publicity of the pagans,

445
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:10,000
 is the gigantic secret of the Christian."

446
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:18,000
 Which just means that while the world is quick to promise and promote that joy is found right here,

447
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:24,000
 the secret is that Christians are the only ones who ever find it.

448
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:29,000
 Christians are the only ones who ever actually find joy.

449
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:33,000
 Why is that? Well, John Mark Comer says, "Joy is more than an emotion.

450
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:37,000
 It is a condition of the heart." It's a condition of the heart.

451
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:41,000
 As he unpacks that idea, he turns to the Sermon on the Mount in Matthew chapter 5,

452
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:43,000
 and he starts working through the Beatitudes.

453
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:46,000
 I remember studying the Beatitudes with a Bible study group,

454
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:48,000
 a group of guys that I was discipling a few years ago.

455
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:50,000
 And as we were working through it, looking at the original language,

456
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:54,000
 that word for blessed, which is blessed are the poor in spirit,

457
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:57,000
 blessed are the meek, blessed are those who mourn,

458
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:59,000
 blessed are those who hunger and thirst for righteousness,

459
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:00,000
 blessed are those who are persecuted.

460
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:06,000
 That word blessed can also be synonymously interpreted as happy,

461
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:09,000
 which just feels odd.

462
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:12,000
 Like, how can I be happy when I'm persecuted?

463
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:16,000
 How can I be happy whenever I'm hungry or thirsty?

464
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:18,000
 How can I be hungry whenever I'm poor in spirit?

465
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:21,000
 How can I be hungry when I'm meek?

466
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:23,000
 Jesus, this doesn't make any sense.

467
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:28,000
 Yet Jesus is saying that your happiness does not depend on what the world does to you.

468
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:31,000
 It depends on what God is doing in you.

469
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:34,000
 That's where your happiness depends.

470
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:37,000
 It depends on what God is doing in you, not what the world does to you.

471
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:40,000
 So what is he doing? What is God doing in your life?

472
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:42,000
 He is making you more like Jesus,

473
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:47,000
 which means he is actively, persistently, and constantly deepening your joy.

474
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:49,000
 That's what he wants.

475
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:56,000
 God is more interested in your joy than you are.

476
00:35:56,000 --> 00:36:00,000
 He wants for your satisfaction more than you do.

477
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:08,000
 And he is begging you to take him up on the offer.

478
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:10,000
 And the reason for that is because in Jesus,

479
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:14,000
 we find not just the feeling of joy, but the fullness of joy.

480
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:18,000
 In Jesus, we find not just the feeling of joy, but the fullness of joy,

481
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:22,000
 that persists through every trial or trouble or tribulation,

482
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:25,000
 that permeates our entire being.

483
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:28,000
 Whether you walk into the office or you go to pick up your mail,

484
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:30,000
 or you're strolling through Trader Joe's,

485
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:32,000
 or you come and sit with your friends,

486
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:36,000
 it doesn't matter where you are, it's permeating your entire being.

487
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:38,000
 But it doesn't just persist or permeate,

488
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:42,000
 it also promotes to the watching world the wonder of the glory of God.

489
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:45,000
 That's the kind of joy he's bringing you into.

490
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:51,000
 Like that's why Jesus says in John 10, 10, "Hey, I came that you might have life."

491
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,000
 He could have just said that.

492
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:57,000
 But he goes further, "That you might have life abundantly."

493
00:36:57,000 --> 00:37:02,000
 John 15, 11, "These things I've spoken to you that my joy might be in you."

494
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:06,000
 But he goes further, "That your joy may be full."

495
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:11,000
 John 16, 24, "Until now you've asked nothing in my name, ask and you will receive."

496
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:15,000
 But he goes further, "That your joy may be full."

497
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:20,000
 John 17, 13, "I am coming to you now, but I say these things that while I am still in the world,

498
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:23,000
 so that they might have not just my joy within them,

499
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:25,000
 but the full measure of my joy within them."

500
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:32,000
 Like Jesus has come not just so you can feel joy, but so you can be joyful.

501
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:38,000
 You understand the difference in feeling joy and being joyful?

502
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:43,000
 I've used this illustration before, but it's the difference in normal acting and method acting.

503
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:49,000
 Like in normal acting, you have someone that looks the part whenever the cameras are rolling.

504
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:55,000
 But in method acting, you have someone that lives the part when the cameras are off.

505
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:57,000
 That's the difference.

506
00:37:57,000 --> 00:38:00,000
 One is the event of acting.

507
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:03,000
 The other is the embodiment of acting.

508
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:05,000
 That's what Jesus wants for you.

509
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:12,000
 Like he wants you to move beyond the event of joy into the embodiment of it.

510
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:14,000
 He doesn't just want you to feel joy.

511
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:21,000
 He wants you to be joyful.

512
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:26,000
 So the natural next question, after hearing all of this,

513
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:28,000
 and I've railed at you and I've yelled at you,

514
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:31,000
 and I've probably annoyed some of you to some extent.

515
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:40,000
 The natural next question is, "Well, then how do we find it?"

516
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:44,000
 That's actually not the natural next question.

517
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:55,000
 Because in asking that, we assume something too important to make any estimations or guesses about,

518
00:38:55,000 --> 00:39:00,000
 which is this, "Do you actually even want it?"

519
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:08,000
 "Do you actually even want this, the kind of joy that Jesus is offering to you?"

520
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:18,000
 Some of you, you don't want full joy.

521
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:20,000
 You don't want full joy.

522
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:26,000
 If you did, if everybody in this room wanted fullness of joy and was ready to go all in with Jesus,

523
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:33,000
 you would be deeply satisfied and I would be without a job.

524
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:38,000
 Lord, I pray that would happen at the porch, because I want you to be joyful.

525
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:42,000
 I want you to go in, all in with him.

526
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:45,000
 But some of you, you don't want full joy.

527
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:47,000
 You want instant gratification.

528
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:49,000
 You want fleeting pleasures.

529
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:55,000
 You want quick coping mechanisms just to make you feel okay for the day.

530
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:59,000
 Here's the thing.

531
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:10,000
 You will be content to try it on your own until you realize just how discontent you are on your own.

532
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:18,000
 You will do your best, but it will never, ever be enough.

533
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:23,000
 But some of you are here.

534
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:26,000
 And you are ready to go all in.

535
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:36,000
 You do want full joy, not joy like the world promises, but the joy that Jesus promises.

536
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,000
 You're ready for that.

537
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:40,000
 You're wanting for that.

538
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:43,000
 You're serious about this.

539
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:48,000
 What you need to know is that Jesus has always been serious about your joy, too.

540
00:40:48,000 --> 00:41:00,000
 He's been so serious about your joy, so much so that the most joyous being in the universe would come to the most joyless beings in the universe.

541
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:11,000
 That happiness from on high would come to our despair down here low.

542
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:22,000
 Jesus wanted you so badly to be a person of joy that he himself would bear in himself all the sorrow of your sin.

543
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:35,000
 You see, Jesus wants to take your bruising, your brokenness, and he wants to mold them, form them, redeem them, reconcile them back into blessings.

544
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:37,000
 He's willing to do whatever it takes.

545
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:40,000
 He might have joy even at the cost of his own life.

546
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:48,000
 He'll come to live the perfect life, but he'll die the death you actually do deserve, for all sin is deserving of condemnation.

547
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:52,000
 And yet he would be condemned in our place that we might find liberation.

548
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:54,000
 We might go free forever.

549
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:56,000
 But that's not all.

550
00:41:56,000 --> 00:42:03,000
 He wants you to find more than a feeling, but the fullness of joy so much so that he won't just give it to you right now.

551
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:05,000
 He won't just give it to you tomorrow.

552
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:06,000
 He won't just give it to you next week.

553
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,000
 He won't just give it to you next month.

554
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:10,000
 He's going to give it to you forever.

555
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:14,000
 He wants to give you eternal, everlasting, infinite joy.

556
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:17,000
 Joy the likes of which you will never grow tired.

557
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:22,000
 Heaven will be far happier than you dare dream.

558
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:25,000
 Like we'll never grow there and get tired of the things we're doing.

559
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:28,000
 It's going to be better and better and better.

560
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:31,000
 Why? Because he is there with us.

561
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:34,000
 And he has come down here to get us.

562
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:41,000
 If you are looking for the fullness of joy, then you need to know the fullness of joy came looking for you.

563
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:43,000
 And his name is Jesus.

564
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:48,000
 And he is looking for some of you tonight.

565
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:50,000
 Is it you?

566
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:53,000
 Let me pray for you.

567
00:42:53,000 --> 00:43:08,000
 Father, I pray with every fiber of my being that these young adults would believe the truth that you want for their happiness,

568
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:16,000
 you want for their joy, you want for their souls satisfaction more than they do.

569
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:24,000
 And I pray God right now, please, that some would take you up on the invitation.

570
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:29,000
 That some would be serious about the opportunity here.

571
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:41,000
 Some would respond for the first time in rejoicing at a king that would come to save even the likes of them.

572
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:51,000
 If you're here and you're serious about journeying into the joy of Jesus,

573
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:55,000
 I'm going to boldly ask you to put your hand up.

574
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:59,000
 To raise it high in declaration to God that God, I want that.

575
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:02,000
 I want you. I want joy. I want Jesus.

576
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:04,000
 That's what I want.

577
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:07,000
 Put it up. Hold it up.

578
00:44:07,000 --> 00:44:09,000
 Look around.

579
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:11,000
 You're not alone.

580
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:13,000
 You are not by yourself.

581
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:17,000
 There are others here that want the same thing you do.

582
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:32,000
 Let us be a people that do not linger behind but lean all the way forward and take God up on the offer that there is deep soul satisfying delight ready for us right now.

583
00:44:32,000 --> 00:44:37,000
 God, we believe that is who you are, that that's what you've come to give.

584
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:39,000
 And that we too can be the same.

585
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:41,000
 We love you. It is in Christ's name we pray.

586
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:43,000
 Amen.

